-- Ricardo Flores May Become Head of Brasilprev, Globo Reports
-- B y   F a b i o l a   M o u r a
-- 2012-05-12T15:01:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-12/ricardo-flores-may-become-head-of-brasilprev-globo-reports.html
Ricardo Flores, the head of  Banco do
Brasil SA ’s employees’ pension fund Previ, may become chief
executive officer of Brasilprev Seguros & Previdencia SA, O
Globo newspaper  reported , without saying how it obtained the
information.  Brasilprev, a pension and insurance unit of Banco do
Brasil, said yesterday its president, Sergio Rosa, resigned,
according to an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fabiola Moura in Sao Paulo at 
 fdemoura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
